<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2619> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2619" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These two Tribunes threatened to prosecute the Consuls if they did not proceed quickly to their provinces, carried a bill that the Senate should appoint an investigator to free any Statelliates still in slavery after the Kalends of Sextilis (Liv. 42.21.4-5 and 8), and forced the oppressor of the Statelliates to come to Rome for trial (42.22.2-4 and 7-8)." .
